This paper deals with topic modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The paper proposes methods for evaluating and improving the quality of topics generated by Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) models. The paper also evaluates the proposed methods on three different datasets, which suggests that the paper could be relevant to multiple sub-categories of computer science. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category, as it deals with NLP and text analysis. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely, as topic modeling is often used in information retrieval tasks such as document clustering and recommendation systems. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category, as topic modeling is a machine learning technique. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible, as topic modeling is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a method for improving the quality of topics. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper proposes a new metric for evaluating topic quality.
